# Deployment

## Context

- When deploying the application, applying migrations to a live database, building production artifacts for release, or restarting/rolling out services.
- When asked to "deploy", "ship", "release", "push to prod", or "update the server".

## Requirements

- **All deployments run on the server, never locally.** The production host is the
  only place where deploy steps (build, migrate, service restart, edge/TLS config)
  are executed. Do not run deployment commands on a developer machine.
- Local machines are for development and verification only: running the dev servers,
  tests, lint/type checks, and the local zero-config SQLite/dev stack.
- Follow the recorded deploy procedure in `.memspec/` (`memspec search deploy`) and the
  `deploy/` scripts on the server. Schema changes are an Alembic deploy step executed
  on the server — never `create_all` outside the gated local bootstrap.
- If a deploy is requested, connect to the production server and run the documented
  procedure there. If server access is unavailable, stop and report it — do not
  improvise a local deployment.

## Examples

<example>
  ```
  // Good — deploy executed on the server
  SSH to the prod host, then run the deploy/ procedure (git pull, build,
  alembic upgrade head, restart services) on the server.
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  ```
  // Bad — building/migrating against production from a local machine
  npm run build && alembic upgrade head   # run locally pointed at prod
  (Violates rule: deployments must run on the server, not locally)
  ```
</example>

## Critical Rules

- Deployments are server-only. Never deploy from a local machine.
- Local = develop, test, verify. Server = build, migrate, release, restart.
- Use the `deploy/` scripts and the `.memspec/` deploy procedure on the server.
